Hi Paul,

Visibility is all about how obvious and &quot;visible&quot; the data and
interactions are between client and server.

The closest opposite is obfuscated.

If you look at the serialized Java objects that are shipped over HTTP
in the DWR (and GWT?)  implementations you should get a strong,
visceral understanding ;)

This is the first characteristic that I judge AJAX toolkits by. If the
HTML/JSON/XML data is visible and the AJAX requests aren&#39;t tunnelling
RPC, then the framework is using REST-inspired techniques of common
data formats and exposing resources.

Mobile code is dangerous because it makes it really easy to screw up
the Visibility of the representations and resources.

John Heintz

